                <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Santoro[/i]
[br]Glad I checked the guides forum - thanks Laeelin this spreadsheet is great. I have a question on a formula, and a few suggestions on Excel based on doing some of the same things with Usul's spreadsheet.

Formula question - Specialization and SCM. You're using (Spec + SCM) / 2000 (where SCM is 0, 50, 100, 200). There's a thread on Graffe's where they tested it and came up with (Spec + SCM)/1750 not /2000. The link is [url]http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm28.showMessageRange?topicID=23.topic[/url]. I haven't tested it myself but it looks like they did a good job.

Excel stuff - for the crazy IF commands, check out CHOOSE. Lets you pick from several things, which makes it a lot easier to do focus levels. ie. IF(Level&lt;=CHOOSE(Focus, 0, 20, 44, 60, 65),1,0)

Also check out INDIRECT. You could give your spec cells labels left of the formula bar (Abj, Alt, etc), and then use INDIRECT.

So the SCM formula in M36 would change from

=0.0005*(IF($G$3=3,200,IF($G$3=2,100,IF($G$3=1,50,0)))+IF(P36=$G$5,$G$6,IF(P36=$H$5,$H$6,IF(P36=$I$5,$I$6,IF(P36=$J$5,$J$6,IF(P36=$K$5,$K$6,0))))))

to something like

=0.0005*(CHOOSE($G$3,0,50,100,200)+INDIRECT(P36))

hope that helps add a few more things
[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
