                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top"><font color="white" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;10/09/2003&nbsp;: 12:42:33 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Laeelin, I think you did crit DD damage slightly wrong.  Crits do not increase the damage done by focus.  Both focus and crits act on the *base* damage of the spell.  So for neuro the average damage should be:<br />1300 + 1300 * crit_percent + 1300 * focus<br />The way you have it now, I think, is:<br />1300 * (1+focus) * (1+crit_percent).<br /><br />So with the numbers in your spreadsheet, neuro would be:<br />1300 + 1300 * 0.13 + 1300 * (0.35/2) = 1697<br /><br />whereas you have 1726<br /><br />Here's a recent thread on graffe's that talks about it:<br /><a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=10141" target="_blank">http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=10141</a></span></font></td>
